	The code below never works.
	The code below adds the word 'exit' to the inventory.
	The code below gets user input repeatedly and 
	adds it to the inventory until the user is done.

	while (input != "exit"){
		cout << "Enter an item: " << endl;
		cin >> input;
		inventory += " " + input;
	}
	You have to make sure your loop stops at some point 
	or your program will run forever.

	The code below is correct.
	The code below has an INFINITE LOOP!

	int i = 0;
